\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}6 sesame bagels\
{\listtext	\'95	}Vegetable Cream Cheese, recipe follows\
{\listtext	\'95	}12 slices {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/smoked-salmon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 smoked salmon}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Slice the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/bagel/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 bagels}} in half horizontally and spread 1 tablespoon of the vegetable cream cheese over the bottom half of each bagel. Arrange 2 slices of smoked salmon over the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream-cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cream cheese}} and place the remaining bagel halves on top. Cut the bagels in half crosswise and serve.\

\b Vegetable Cream Cheese:
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}16 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons minced scallions, white and green parts\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons finely chopped carrot\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons finely chopped {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 celery}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons finely chopped radish (2 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/radish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 radishes}})\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 to 3 pinches kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pinch finely ground black pepper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Place the cream cheese, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/scallion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 scallions}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/carrot/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 carrot}}, celery, radish, salt, and pepper in the bowl of an electric {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mixer}} fitted with the paddle attachment and mix on low speed until blended.\

\fs32 Yield: 6 servings}